@mcserra Looks like we can drop !corsConfig.origins.get().contains("*") because we have corsConfig.origins.get().contains(origin) which ensures the precise match, but instead we should check that the Origin header does no contain *.
This will ensure that, assuming Origin is something like https://origin, then if we have the allowed origins as https://origin,* then true will be returned due to a precise match.
Do you agree ?

